[Primary Tumour][pTX: Primary Tumour cannot be assessed]
[Primary Tumour][pT0: No evidence of primary tumour]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Hypopharynx][pT1: Tumour limited to one subsite of hypopharynx and/or 2 cm or less in greatest dimension]

[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Hypopharynx][pT2: Tumour invades more than one subsite of hypopharynx or an adjacent site, or measures more than 2 cm but not more than 4 cm in greatest dimension, without fixation of hemilarynx]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Hypopharynx][pT3: Tumour more than 4 cm in greatest dimension, or with fixation of hemilarynx or extension to oesophagus]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Hypopharynx][pT4a: Tumour invades any of the following: thyroid/cricoid cartilage, hyoid bone, thyroid gland, oesophagus, central compartment soft tissue*]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Hypopharynx][pT4b: Tumour invades prevertebral fascia, encases carotid artery, or invades mediastinal structures]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Supraglottis][pT1: Tumour limited to one subsite of supraglottis with normal vocal cord mobility]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Supraglottis][pT2: Tumour invades mucosa of more than one adjacent subsite of supraglottis or glottis or region outside the supraglottis]

[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Supraglottis][pT3: Tumour limited to larynx with vocal cord fixation and/or invades any of the following: postcricoid area, pre epiglottic space, paraglottic space, and/or inner cortex of thyroid cartilage]

[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Supraglottis][pT4a: Tumour invades through the thyroid cartilage and/or invades tissues beyond the larynx, e.g., trachea, soft tissues of neck including deep/extrinsic muscle of tongue]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Supraglottis][pT4b: Tumour invades prevertebral space, encases carotid artery, or mediastinal structures]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT1: Tumour limited to vocal cord(s)]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT1: Tumour limited to vocal cord(s)][pT1a: Tumour limited to one vocal cord]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT1: Tumour limited to vocal cord(s)][pT1b: Tumour involves both vocal cords]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT2: Tumour extends to supraglottis and/or subglottis, and/or with impaired vocal cord mobility]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT3: Tumour limited to larynx with vocal cord fixation and/or invades paraglottic space, and/or inner cortex of the thyroid cartilage]

[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT4a: Tumour invades through the outer cortex of the thyroid cartilage, and/or invades tissues beyond the larynx, e.g., trachea, soft tissues of neck including deep/extrinsic muscle of tongue]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Glottis][pT4b: Tumour invades prevertebral space, encases carotid artery, or mediastinal structures]
[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Subglottis][pT1: Tumour limited to subglottis]

[Primary Tumour][Primary tumour: Subglottis][pT3: Tumour limited to larynx with vocal cord fixation]

[Regional lymph nodes][Histological examination of a selective neck dissection specimen will ordinarily include 10 or more lymph nodes. Histological examination of a radical or modified radical neck dissection specimen will ordinarily include 15 or more lymph nodes.]
[Regional lymph nodes][pNX: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed]
[Regional lymph nodes][pN0: No regional lymph node metastasis]
[Regional lymph nodes][pN1: Metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension without extranodal extension]

[Regional lymph nodes][pN2a: Metastasis in a single ipsilateral lymph node, less than 3 cm in greatest dimension with extranodal extension or more than 3 cm but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension without extranodal extension]
[Regional lymph nodes][pN2b: Metastasis in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension, without extranodal extension]
[Regional lymph nodes][pN2c: Metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension, without extranodal extension]
[Regional lymph nodes][pN3a: Metastasis in a lymph node more than 6 cm in greatest dimension without extranodal extension]

[Regional lymph nodes][pN3b: Metastasis in a lymph node more than 3 cm in greatest dimension with extranodal extension or multiple ipsilateral, or any contralateral or bilateral node(s) with extranodal extension]
